SIMPLE: unawares
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unawares
<hw>Un`a*wares"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Without design
or preparation; suddenly; without premeditation, unexpectedly.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Mercies lighting <xex>unawares</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. H.
Newman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest <qex>unawares</qex> we lose⟦br⟧
This our high place, our sanctuary, our hill.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><mcol><col><b>At unaware</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>At
unawares</b></col></mcol>, <cd>unexpectedly; by surprise.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He breaks <qex>at unawares</qex> upon our walks.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So we met⟦br⟧
In this old sleepy town <qex>at unaware</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>R.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Unbacked</ent>⟦br⟧
